              Going through the previous games and reached here. I can't understand the criticism both Whoscored and Messi getting - former for the supposed bug in their system and the latter for being not scoring. Please check the following stats: Players - Total shots - Goals on target - Hit on bar - Blocked - Off target Barca - 23 - 2 - 1 - 10 - 11 Messi - 7 - 2 - 1 - 3 - 1 Rest - 16 - 0 - 0 - 6 - 10 Surely, Messi was not at his best - but he was still the most effective player on the pitch by far along with Naldo. And I do think it is Naldo who deserved to be the MoM in that game. Having said that, I do believe Whoscored gives a bit more weightage to dribbles and doesn't give much weightage to shots off target (negative). And if the latter was introduced, the forwards would not be getting as much rating as what we are seeing now. Also increase the weightage for overall a bit to balance the reductions and we will see a rating system with much more justice.
